Collaboration with Ilug-d for some talks/workshops?

1. propose collab to ilug-d. 23 May - 27 June some weekend.
2. on acceptance send out call for speakers in pyj
3. go listen to collab talk.

# Todo

- [x] 28 June 1630 : 1900 hrs
- [x] @thesage21 send out cfp for representing pyj in ilugd collab. 1 speaker slot available.
- ~~[ ] Find supporting speaker for #101~~
- [x] Ilugd will present ILUGD/talks#176

# Proposed message

We'll be collaborating with [India Linux Users Group Delhi](https://www.linuxdelhi.org/) this month.

There will be two talks. One speaker will be from their end and one speaker will be from PyJaipur.
This event will be broadcast on both PyJaipur and ILUG-D social platforms.

Anyone who would like to represent PyJaipur for this collaboration is welcome to post a message in the telegram group or on [github issue #78](https://github.com/PyJaipur/PyJaipur/issues/78) .
You'll receive help from the entire PyJaipur community while preparing your talk if you need it so go and propose a talk!

Ladies are especially encouraged to participate in this event!

---

@Shivank98 @ayushisaxena22050 @nk521 does this sound ok? I was thinking of adding a give away for this. I have t-shirts left over from last year's SOA.

Yes ..!!
This sounds great.
Are you talking about monthly meetup context?
For the topic part and ladies participations part I have few suggestions:

1.we may ask Preeti  for a talk as she is doing some good work in pytorch
and deep learning.

2. I can prepare a talk myself on Flask framework.

3. I know someone who is interested to give a talk but do it necessarily be
on python related topics.
